      {
        "id": 2311790,
        "name": null,
        "username": "jcoley3",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/jcoley3/{size}/507_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-12-08T06:33:44.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This is the best producer of White Burgundy I can think of that is mostly unknown here.</p>\n<p>So lock the thread, please. And edit your posts.</p>\n<p>More seriously, when I was at a Vintage 59 trade show in Chicago about six years ago, one of the two tables I went back to more for enjoyment than edification was the Bash Bros, especially the Puligny village wine. The Chassagne is almost as good, and less expensive.</p>\n<p>But lock the thread and delete your posts.</p>",
