      {
        "id": 2312167,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-12-08T18:36:52.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The Bachelet brothers are also still in an upward trajectory. 2016 is not a great white Burgundy vintage, but their Folati\u00e8res is one of the best Puligny 1er Crus I tasted.</p>\n<p>The red Maranges Fussi\u00e8re is superb value, especially in 2015.</p>",
